      <h1 class='title'>Rehabilitation</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1683WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1683ws' title='Col. 1683WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1683WS' name='column_1683ws' href='#column_1683ws' rel='bookmark'>1683WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_186'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-keith-bradley' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_186' title='Link to this speech by Mr Keith Bradley' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-keith-bradley" title="Mr Keith Bradley">Mr. Keith Bradley</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department when he will publish the National Rehabilitation Action Plan. [188084]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_187'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-paul-goggins' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_187' title='Link to this speech by Mr Paul Goggins' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-paul-goggins" title="Mr Paul Goggins">Paul Goggins</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para"><span class="italic">[holding answer 13 September 2004]:</span> On 19 July 2004, I published the National Reducing Re-offending Action Plan. Over 60 action points have been agreed across Government, covering all the key areas to support the rehabilitation of offenders, in a concerted effort to reduce re-offending. For each agreed action point, the Plan suggests complementary activity for the consideration of those working at the regional and local level. Copies of have been placed in the Library of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
